1. TypeScript strict mode is enabled. Never use `any` type without an explicit `// eslint-disable` comment explaining why.

2. Never hardcode secrets, API keys, passwords, or connection strings. Always use environment variables.

3. All API route handlers must validate input with Zod before processing. Never trust `req.body`, `req.query`, or `req.params`.

4. Use Prisma query builder for all database access. Never construct raw SQL with string interpolation.

